President Biden and President Putin held a video call to discuss various issues between the U.S. and Russia. Biden expressed concerns about Russia's military buildup near Ukraine and emphasized that the U.S. and its allies would respond with strong economic measures if there was a military escalation. Biden reiterated support for Ukraine's sovereignty and called for de-escalation and diplomacy. The two leaders assigned their teams to follow up on these discussions. They also talked about the U.S.-Russia dialogue on Strategic Stability, a separate dialogue on ransomware, and cooperation on regional matters like Iran.